		<xp:panel>
			<a name="whatis" />
			<xp:panel tagName="div"
				style="font-weight:bold;margin:0 0 5px 0;">
				What is CardScanR
			</xp:panel>
			<xp:panel>
				CardScanR is a Contact Management application build on
				IBM Lotus Domino using XPages.
				<xp:br />
				<xp:br />
				CardScanR was originally developed by&#160;
				<a href="http://quintessens.wordpress.com/"
					target="_blank">
					Patrick Kwinten
				</a>

				<xp:br />
				<xp:br />
				For more information about the project or to download
				the latest release visit the&#160;
				<xp:link escape="true" text="project page" id="link2">
					<xp:this.value><![CDATA[http://www.openntf.org/internal/home.nsf/project.xsp?action=openDocument&name=CardScanR]]></xp:this.value>
				</xp:link>
				&#160;on OpenNTF.
			</xp:panel>
		</xp:panel>
		<xp:panel style="margin:10px 0 0 0;">
			<a name="openntf" />
			<xp:panel style="font-weight:bold;margin:0 0 5px 0;">
				What isÂ OpenNTF?
			</xp:panel>

			OpenNTF is a community devoted to enabling groups of
			individuals all over the world to collaborate on IBM Lotus
			Notes/Domino applications and release them as open source.
			<xp:br />
			<xp:br />
			Visit the&#160;
			<xp:link escape="true" text="OpenNTF" id="link1"
				value="http://www.openntf.org" />
			&#160;website&#160;to read more this community&#160;and find
			interesting projects to download.
		</xp:panel>



		<xp:panel style="margin:10px 0 0 0;">
			<a name="contribute"></a>
			<xp:panel style="font-weight:bold;margin:0 0 5px 0;">
				How can I contribute?
			</xp:panel>
			You can contribute on the positive side
			(idea's,&#160;suggestions for improvement) and the negative
			side&#160;(errors, bugs) of CardScanR.
			<xp:br />
			<xp:br />
			Please use the&#160;<xp:link escape="true" text="project page" id="link4">
					<xp:this.value><![CDATA[http://www.openntf.org/internal/home.nsf/project.xsp?action=openDocument&name=CardScanR]]></xp:this.value>
				</xp:link>&#160;on OpenNTF to do this.
			<xp:br />
			<xp:br />
			We will also post 'help wanted' posts here to ask assistance
			to improve CardScanR.
		</xp:panel>

